at|

^*BWhich Suit to Lead (in order of preference).^*N
Always lead your partner's suit. If you do not lead partner's suit, partner can assume you have a void.   
Unbid suit. 
Longest suit, (against NT contracts--fourth best).
Suits with an honor sequence
Trump
Singleton. You should either have a trump trick or good reason to believe partner may have the Ace or a trump trick.|
PG| ***** 5 ***** |


AT|

^*BWhich Suit Leads to Avoid^*N
Opponents' suits.
Away from an unprotected honor,(except for longest suit in no trump).
Away from an Ace in a suit contract. In the rare case where you decide you must lead the suit, you should lead the Ace. In no trump, it is often right to lead away from an Ace.
Doubletons (except in partner's suit or trump).|
