^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Simple. The J109 of spades are in dummy. If West can get East to ruff a heart with the (hopefully) eight of spades, then South  will be forced to overruff with a higher spade. Since the J109 are in dummy, that means South  has to use the Ace or King of spades to overruff--declarer does not have any card higher in his hand. That means that West's Queen of spades will become good. |
