^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I would not hate it if South bid 1N instead of 2D, but most would bid 2D. Now, one misconception that some people have is that 2D is forcing. That is not true. 2D can absolutely be passed. A new suit by responder is absolutely forcing. So as long as responder keeps introducing new suits, opener cannot pass. However, a non-jump new suit by opener is not forcing. The only way for opener to force is to either reverse or jump shift. In order to jump shift South needs at least a good 18 points.|
